AI Stocks Slip As Microsoft & Google Earnings Disappoint Investors
column9:
AI Stocks Slip As Microsoft & Google Earnings Disappoint Investors 

Artificial Intelligence-related stocks saw a significant downturn yesterday, wiping out $190 billion in the US market value, following underwhelming earnings reports from major players. Google-parent Alphabet saw a 5.6% drop in shares after ad revenue missed forecasts, emphasising the high cost of AI competitiveness. Microsoft, though surpassing revenue forecasts, faced a 1% share dip due to anticipated substantial capital costs for AI infrastructure. Chipmaker AMD also fell 6% as its first-quarter revenue forecast fell short of expectations. Elsewhere in Asia, Samsung shares declined over 1%, after reporting a 34% drop in Q4 profit.
